## III. System Architecture

The proposed GeoAI framework is structured as a five-stage pipeline:

```
[ Raw Raster Inputs ]
        │
        ▼
[ GIS Preprocessing ]
  - Alignment to reference grid (EPSG:32643, 30m)
  - Drainage channel extraction (Flow Acc threshold)
  - Proximity & density rasters
        │
        ▼
[ Input Stack Assembly ]
  - DEM | Slope | Flow | DistDrainage |
    DrainageDensity | BuiltupDensity | Rainfall scalar
        │
        ▼
[ U-Net CNN Training ]
  - Patch-based extraction (64×64)
  - Balanced sampling (50% flood / 50% non-flood)
  - Ground truth: Sentinel-1 SAR Flood Mask 2018
        │
        ▼
[ Inference Engine ]
  - Sliding-window tile-based full-raster inference
  - Rainfall scalar injected per-tile at test time
  - Output: Flood Probability GeoTIFF
        │
        ▼
[ Web Dashboard ]
  - FastAPI REST backend
  - Leaflet.js interactive map
  - Rainfall slider, place search, alert logic
```

**Fig. 1.** End-to-end GeoAI pipeline from raw DEM to interactive flood risk dashboard.

